data.title: Kris Jenner will ‘never marry’ boyfriend of three years Corey Gamble
data.meta_description: Sources close to Kardashian matriarch Kris Jenner revealed that the star will 'never get married' to Corey Gamble, despite their committed relationship.
data.text:
Even though Kris Jenner has been dating boyfriend Corey Gamble for almost three years, she reportedly has no plans to marry him.

A source close to Jenner told People that "Kris is still seeing Corey. Sometimes they seem fine and sometimes not great," adding that the "relationship is more business than romantic."

"Kris is basically his sugar mama," the source said of the pair, who have been together since November 2014.

The source added, "They will never get married."

See photos of Kris Jenner and Corey Gamble together:

This is in line with what Jenner told Ellen DeGeneres earlier in the year when she appeared on DeGeneres' show in February.

"You know, I've done that twice and it didn't work out so well," she said at the time. "So I don't know — you never know. I'm going to take a page out of Goldie and Kurt's book. Or Kourtney's book. I think as long as things are going so well, why ruffle it up?"

Additionally, the same People source said that Jenner is looking forward to becoming a grandmother again after news broke that Kanye West and Kim Kardashian are looking forward to a third child, for which they will be using a surrogate.

Jenner, according to the source, is relieved that Kardashian will not be going through another pregnancy after the last one caused such problems as she suffered from placenta accreta.

"Kris will be very excited about another baby and thinks using a surrogate is a great idea," the source said.
